# AusMT deploy environment. Copy to `.env` in THIS directory (deploy/) before running compose:
#   cp deploy/.env.example deploy/.env   # then edit the values below
# `docker compose` auto-loads a sibling `.env`; `make` reads AUSMT_DATA_DIR from the shell too.
#
# Only the REQUIRED-ALWAYS block is needed for a portal-only deploy. The GATEWAY block is needed
# ONLY if you bring up the submission gateway (`docker compose --profile gateway up -d`). The
# OPTIONAL-TUNING block can be left entirely unset — every one of those has a working default.
#
# NOTE: keep `.env` OUT of version control (it can hold secrets). Add `deploy/.env` to .gitignore.

# =============================================================================================
# REQUIRED ALWAYS  (portal + everything — compose keeps a hard ${VAR:?} guard on these two)
# =============================================================================================

# Host root for ALL persistent AusMT state: site-data/ (generated portal tree, container-written
# as uid 10001) and surveys-live/ (the ausmt-surveys git checkout the engine reads). Must pre-exist
# with the ownership the preflight/README describe. `make preflight` checks it.
# C40: the serve-reconcile timer (deploy/systemd/ausmt-reconcile.service) reads this via its
# EnvironmentFile=<deploy>/.env — the reconcile script locates surveys-live/, site-data/, and the
# gateway state dir under it. `make` also reads it here now (the Makefile's `-include .env`).
AUSMT_DATA_DIR=/srv/ausmt

# GHCR namespace (org or user) the images were published under by deploy-images.yml, e.g. images
# resolve to ghcr.io/OWNER/ausmt-portal:TAG. No working default — set the real GitHub org/user.
OWNER=REPLACE_WITH_GHCR_OWNER

# Image tag to pull/run for all services. "latest" tracks the newest push to main; pin to a release
# tag (e.g. v0.3.0) for a reproducible, deliberately-upgraded deploy. Defaults to "latest" if unset.
TAG=latest

# =============================================================================================
# GATEWAY PROFILE  (only for `docker compose --profile gateway up -d`)
# Compose no longer hard-guards these (C33): a portal-only deploy never needs them. But the gateway
# will not FUNCTION without them — the app/runner fail-close instead of compose. `make preflight
# PROFILE=gateway` checks them.
# =============================================================================================

# Operator-issued submission key, >= 16 chars. Testers send it as the X-AusMT-Submit-Key header.
# The gateway app REFUSES TO START if it is unset or < 16 chars (fail closed, design §3). A real
# secret — keep it out of git, rotate it if a tester leaves. Generate one:
#   python3 -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
AUSMT_SUBMIT_KEY=REPLACE_WITH_A_LONG_RANDOM_KEY

# Path to THIS repo's checkout on the box (the dir holding gateway/, engine/, deploy/). The
# gw-runner bind-mounts ${AUSMT_CODE_DIR}/gateway read-only into the engine image (which does not
# ship the gateway package). Normally the same checkout you run compose/make from. If unset, the
# gateway profile fails at the runner (it cannot import `gateway`) — portal-only never needs it.
# C40: the serve-reconcile timer reads this via its EnvironmentFile=<deploy>/.env too — the
# reconcile script runs `make -C $AUSMT_CODE_DIR/deploy rebuild-data`, so it must point at THIS
# checkout (the one holding deploy/). Set it whenever you install the reconcile timer.
AUSMT_CODE_DIR=/srv/ausmt/code

# Curator credentials for the C11 curator UI: comma-separated name:key pairs, each key >= 16 chars.
# Each key authenticates a NAMED curator so every approve/return/reject is attributable. SEPARATE
# from AUSMT_SUBMIT_KEY. The curator routes return 503 (fail closed) until this is set and
# well-formed; the submit half works regardless. A real secret — never logged. Generate a key:
#   python3 -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
# e.g.  AUSMT_CURATOR_KEYS=ben:LONG_RANDOM_KEY_1,amy:LONG_RANDOM_KEY_2
AUSMT_CURATOR_KEYS=

# Directory holding git PUSH credentials for the C11 publish flow (a deploy-key ssh dir with
# known_hosts, or a git credential file) — bind-mounted READ-ONLY at /srv/git-creds. This is how the
# container's `git push` authenticates to the surveys-live origin WITHOUT a secret in .env or the
# image. Leave unset to validate compose against the committed placeholder (push then fails =>
# PUBLISH_FAILED, fail closed) until you point it at real creds. Do NOT put a token in .env.
# AUSMT_GIT_CREDS_DIR=/srv/ausmt/git-creds

# =============================================================================================
# OPTIONAL TUNING  (env-only; every one has a working default — leave unset unless you must change
# it. compose.yaml FORWARDS each of these into the container(s) that consume it as ${VAR:-DEFAULT}
# — so setting one here reaches the app, and leaving it unset resolves to the SAME default the code
# uses. compose never HARD-guards (${VAR:?}) these: a portal-only deploy resolves with them all unset.
# The "consumed by" tag on each names which compose SERVICE the value is forwarded to.)
# =============================================================================================

# C18 build-cache size cap in MB (engine/extract/cache.py). Pruned oldest-first at the end of each
# successful build. Default 2048.
# consumed by: build-runner (the engine-build service the cache accelerates).
# AUSMT_CACHE_MAX_MB=2048

# C31 metadata-editor poll timeout in seconds — how long the gateway waits for the gw-runner to
# process an edit job before surfacing a retryable error (gateway/config.py). Default 120.
# consumed by: gateway.
# AUSMT_EDIT_TIMEOUT_S=120

# Gateway upload/queue limits (gateway/config.py, gateway/runner). Defaults shown.
# AUSMT_MAX_UPLOAD_MB=250       # max accepted upload size          — consumed by: gateway AND gw-runner
#                               #   (they MUST match: the runner derives its extraction byte-cap from it)
# AUSMT_MAX_INFLIGHT=8          # max concurrent in-flight submissions — consumed by: gateway
# AUSMT_MAX_PER_DAY=25          # per-submitter daily cap              — consumed by: gateway
# AUSMT_JOB_TIMEOUT_S=900       # per-job wall-clock timeout in the runner — consumed by: gateway AND gw-runner
# AUSMT_CLAMD_HOST=clamd        # clamd hostname on the compose network — consumed by: gateway
# AUSMT_CLAMD_PORT=3310         # clamd INSTREAM port                  — consumed by: gateway

# Curator session / login-throttle tuning (gateway/config.py). Defaults shown.
# consumed by: gateway (all three).
# AUSMT_SESSION_TTL_S=43200     # curator session absolute expiry (12 h)
# AUSMT_LOGIN_MAX_ATTEMPTS=5    # failed-login attempts before throttling
# AUSMT_LOGIN_WINDOW_S=300      # throttle window in seconds

# Nightly backup tuning (deploy/backup.sh, run by ausmt-backup.timer via this EnvironmentFile).
# Both have working defaults — set them here only if you keep backups elsewhere or want a different
# retention. The DB is snapshotted WAL-safe into a per-timestamp dir; .env + surveys-live are NEVER
# backed up (secrets live in your password manager; surveys-live's backup is GitHub). See
# README "Backups & restore".
# consumed by: the ausmt-backup timer (NOT a container — these are not forwarded into compose).
# AUSMT_BACKUP_DIR=/srv/ausmt/backups   # backups root (default: $AUSMT_DATA_DIR/backups)
# AUSMT_BACKUP_RETAIN=14                 # on-box snapshots to keep (default 14)

# External alerting (deploy/scripts/alert.sh, run by ausmt-alert.timer via this EnvironmentFile).
# The box pings an EXTERNAL dead-man monitor (healthchecks.io class) every 15 min: a success beat when
# all checks pass, a fail ping (with the failure summary) otherwise. The SERVICE routes the alert email
# to the curator — so who gets alerted is changed in the service dashboard, NEVER here. See
# README "Alerting" for the one-time check + email setup.
# consumed by: the ausmt-alert timer (NOT a container — not forwarded into compose).
#
# The service ping URL. Confidential-ish (anyone with it can spoof a beat) but NON-privileged (it grants
# no access to the box or any data) — so it lives HERE in .env (gitignored, password-manager-canonical),
# NOT in git. UNSET/EMPTY (the default) => alert.sh prints a loud "not configured" note and exits 0, so
# the timer can be installed before you create the external check. Paste the URL the service gives you:
# AUSMT_ALERT_URL=https://hc-ping.com/REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-CHECK-UUID
#
# Thresholds — all have working defaults; set only to tune. A check FAILS (=> fail ping) when:
# AUSMT_ALERT_DISK_PCT=85            # the $AUSMT_DATA_DIR filesystem is over this %% used (default 85)
# AUSMT_ALERT_RECONCILE_MAX_MIN=45  # reconcile-status.json last_run is older than this many min, or
#                                   #   action=failed (default 45 — three missed 15-min reconcile ticks)
# AUSMT_ALERT_BACKUP_MAX_H=26       # the newest backup snapshot is older than this many hours (default
#                                   #   26 — a daily backup + a couple of hours of slack)
# AUSMT_ALERT_PAUSE_MAX_H=24        # (C43 S2b-ii) auto-rebuild PAUSED for this many hours CUMULATIVE
#                                   #   (continuous span, re-arm-proof) fails a check + ops-floor amber
#                                   #   (default 24) — an attacker can't silently keep serving frozen

# Curator ACTIONS agent (C43 S2b-ii — deploy/scripts/actions.sh, run by ausmt-actions.timer via this
# EnvironmentFile). It executes the privileged workbench intents the gateway writes (update / backup /
# rollback / restore). Every action is single-flight locked + audited (gateway/state/actions-audit.log).
# consumed by: the ausmt-actions timer (NOT a container — not forwarded into compose).
# PRE-NCI: the update + restore recipes are flagged for the pre-NCI hostile re-audit (record D9.6) —
# do NOT enable ausmt-actions.timer on an internet-facing box before that audit passes.
# AUSMT_ACTIONS_RATELIMIT_S=30      # per-kind cooldown (s): a repeat intent inside this window is
#                                   #   refused + audited (default 30; 0 disables). Attack-signal guard.
# AUSMT_ACTIONS_LOCK=/srv/ausmt/actions.lock   # single-flight lock path (default $AUSMT_DATA_DIR/actions.lock)
# (AUSMT_ACTIONS_COMPOSE / _GIT / _BACKUP / _DRILL are TEST SHIM hooks only — leave unset in production.)

# Serve-reconcile pause expiry (C43 S2b-ii — deploy/scripts/reconcile.sh). A curator pause.flag older
# than this is IGNORED (auto-expires) so a forgotten pause never freezes serving forever.
# AUSMT_RECONCILE_PAUSE_EXPIRY_MIN=360   # minutes (default 360 = 6 h)

# Build cache mode (C43 S2b-ii Force-full-rebuild — deploy/Makefile rebuild-data). reconcile.sh sets
# this to `refresh` for a curator "Force full rebuild"; leave unset for the normal cached `rw` build.
# AUSMT_BUILD_CACHE_MODE=rw          # rw (default) | refresh (recompute all, no cache reuse) | ro

# Usage-analytics aggregator (C45 — deploy/scripts/aggregate_stats.py, run daily by ausmt-stats.timer
# via this EnvironmentFile). Everything below DEFAULTS under $AUSMT_DATA_DIR — set an override only if
# your layout differs. A missing db-ip CSV is NOT fatal (country -> "unknown"); see README "Usage
# analytics" for placing/refreshing it. The aggregator stores AGGREGATES ONLY — never an address or UA.
# AUSMT_STATS_DBIP_CSV=/srv/ausmt/geoip/dbip-country-lite.csv  # db-ip IP-to-Country Lite CSV (CC-BY-4.0)
#                                   #   (default $AUSMT_DATA_DIR/geoip/dbip-country-lite.csv)
# AUSMT_STATS_LOG_DIR=/srv/ausmt/logs/caddy      # Caddy access-log dir (default $AUSMT_DATA_DIR/logs/caddy)
# AUSMT_STATS_MANIFEST=...           # served download manifest (default $AUSMT_DATA_DIR/site-data/current/manifest.json)
# AUSMT_STATS_FILE=...               # the cumulative stats.json (default $AUSMT_DATA_DIR/gateway/state/stats.json)
# AUSMT_STATS_DAILY_KEEP=90          # daily-series tail length kept in stats.json (default 90)
# (AUSMT_STATS_NOW is a TEST hook for deterministic folds — leave unset in production.)

# NOTE: AUSMT_VALIDATOR_PATH, AUSMT_GW_DATA, AUSMT_SURVEYS_LIVE and other container-internal paths
# are set INSIDE compose.yaml / the images — do NOT put them here.
